    "body": "@amohamedali when attempting to repro on linux: Using a java client talking to a local ruby server, and a ruby server shutdown in the middle of the inactive part of a bidi call (during a 30-second to 1 minute gap between messages in a bidi call), the java client _does_ seem to get notified of an end to the connection, as expected. \n\nIs it possible that there is another grpc server listening on the same port, on the same machine (which one the client gets connected to would be determined by the server's OS)? If this were the case, then shutting down the server that the client _wasn't_ connected to wouldn't cause any errors.\n"
