    "created_at": "2016-10-24T13:31:52Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-24T13:31:52Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi sorry for being late to answer I really wanted to test things in different conditions to check when it really does fails, and this issue actually doesn't happen in a local environment, or if the client and the server are on a private network.\nThis makes me think that it's most likely a router in between the server and the client that closes the connection if nothing happens when there is no communication for too long.\nI have looked into issues on the grpc-java side and found out that it is missing a \"keep-alive\" option on the tcp socket and that there is an issue to fix that, so I will wait until this is validated and if it still doesn't help I will come back here to keep you informed.Btw the grpc-java issue I am talking about is this one : https://github.com/grpc/grpc-java/pull/2366\n"
  },
